[36:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'understand text like this. For computers, you need to feed it numbers. So traditional large language models what they need to do is actually convert all this text into tokens or basically numbers to be fed through the AI model for training and inference. The problem'

[36:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is using these text tokens especially for extremely long text like if you want to feed it an entire novel then it becomes very computationally expensive very quickly like the amount of compute'

[36:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
